# Plan to Teach and Engineer Prism as an Autonomous Web Builder

This plan outlines the conceptual architecture, development steps, and training loops required to engineer **PRISM** so that it can autonomously design, program, refine, and validate complex, linked document systems (such as multi-page glassmorphic websites) out in production. It enables PRISM to utilize its own specialized environment—the **Prism IDE**—to write, compile, lint, and audit code in the same task-driven, self-healing manner as world-class agent runtime environments.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Enabling the Self-Contained Prism IDE Workspace**
> In production, the agent must be able to write and inspect code files without manual operator intervention. We propose introducing a dedicated **Prism IDE toolset** (offering granular block replacements, file syntax validation, and instant test builds) integrated directly into the `Tools & Plugins` dashboard interface.

> [!WARNING]
> **Governance Approvals for Sandbox Shell Execution**
> Because visual audits require launching a headless Playwright/Chrome browser, the agent will execute background sandboxed shell processes. These are governed under `tier2_conditional` policies and require pre-signed token authorization profiles in corporate environments.

